texts.text: Ugh... It's so cold...
Put on a coat, a jacket or something?
Really, you're giving me that? Don't you know how expensive they are?
Mr. Meat with his blub...
inner lining for dealing with cold weather.
Wait, you were about to say blubber!
Anyways, is this really the best we can do?
Just doing more patrols around here and all.
It's dull and I feel like there's more we can do...
But we still don't have a solution for those demons.
For now, all we can do is gather as much new information as we can... Wah!
[sys user_name], don't stop so suddenly like that!
We need to keep going a while little longer.
The darkness is spreading.
I'm done.
!! Wait...
>Seiran scans her surroundings.
What do you mean done? Wait...
Was that darkness already out this far?
Is it spreading?
It is. It's out further than it was yesterday.
>From the deep within the thickening darkness, a demon look on menacingly...
Shit. We still don't have a plan for striking back.
And they're coming.
>The darkness created more space for demons to appear as it keeps spreading.
*Growl*
*Groan*
Devil Download!
Take this! First strike!
*Shriek*
>The demons disappear!
*Moan*
*Growl*
>They regain their strength...!
Damn, it's not working! We need to fall back!
I'll keep the big guy busy while the rest of you get out of the darkness!
Okay... Wait, what?!
*Snicker*
*Roar*
>Demons appear behind you!
We're surrounded.
Can't go forward. We got no plan even if we do.
Newbie and I will hold the front. Seiran and Ririn, hold the rear!
What if the ones behind us can't be killed either?!
Just keep trying!
The darkness keeps creeping in. At this rate, we'll be swallowed whole!
Goddammit!
*Shriek*
*Moan*
*Hiss*
Crap, it's not working!
At this rate, we're all gonna...!
Fear not. I shall fight in your stead.
What...?!
>A blinding flash of light engulfs your surroundings!
>It's so bright, you keep your eyes closed...!
>The light recedes...
Huh? What? What just happened?
The darkness, the demons... They're all gone.
But who...?
That would be Baldur the God of Light.
Such brilliance... The redeeming light...!
We expect no less from the great Baldur!
Are you the ones that saved us?
You have our gratitude. Thank you very much.
Oh, not I. It was but Baldur the God of Light.
A demon? Are you Dx2?
Dx2? What is that?
No matter. Please tell me about yourselves and what has happened.
It seems like your devices allow you to wield some uncanny powers.
They look like smartphones, but are they magical artifacts?
What do we say...?
They saved us. We should tell them what we can.
They might even be able to help us.
That's about it...
I see. Liberators... I was not aware that such a group existed.
Protecting this world by using the powers of beings that are not human
sounds very similar to what we do.
Yes, I agree.
Which is why I'd like to suggest that we work together to solve this crisis...
Ah, but there is no need for you to fight anymore.
Huh?
Yes. The God of Light, Baldur himself, shall be the one that saves this world!
Your powers are indeed remarkable,
but they were naught in the face of this evil.
If it was not for Baldur, you would all be dead.
Is it not clear that this world is doomed without Baldur?
Which is why it'd be best to leave this matter to Baldur.
You should be glad.
You have no need to put yourselves in such danger anymore.
Uh, yeah...
It's true we couldn't do anything, and my ears can't take much more of this...
That is enough...
Liberators, I will gladly accept your aid.
B-Baldur?! Wait!
They were powerless!
Your brilliance alone was what vanquished this evil...!
Indeed. But they are also the light that stands up to this darkness.
You as well possess this light.
B-but... Because we brought you back to life, Baldur, so that...!
Seiran! Emergency! Please respond!
Seiran here. What's going on?
It's bad yo.
The places in Akihabara that y'all were keepin' an eye on...
Well, darkness started spreadin' from places other than those.
Yo, a lot of places.
What?!
People are posting photos on social media sites and saying these places are haunted.
No one seems to have gotten hurt or anything yet though...
Does that mean these unkillable demons are showing up there too?
Can't say without actually goin' there first.
Yo, the Tokyo Branch can't deal with somethin' on this scale.
I've been tryin' to get a hold of other branches to come and help.
Shiang Sun and I need to stay here to keep things rollin'.
Got it. We're heading back too.
Is there a problem...?
Yes. Those demons and darkness are appearing all over the place now.
What...?!
We need to head back to our hideout to come up with a plan.
If you'll excuse us.
>The Liberators take their leave...
But only Baldur's radiant light can bring peace to this disaster.
It will not matter how many of their brethren they can muster.
And yet... Why is it that they fight on so desperately?
No matter...
Let us be on our way as well, Baldur.
